<subSubSection id="430179BB7028E22446F9FB74C1663874" pageId="17" pageNumber="110" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="E47083A1C6F7EE99E9D06F12AD377AED" pageId="17" pageNumber="110">Discussion.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="6B6111818D2581A5E4DC34C93BAC3C1F" pageId="17" pageNumber="110">
<taxonomicName id="425A581DF0DFE4EE50AD742B3C2FA434" class="Lycopodiopsida" family="Selaginellaceae" genus="Selaginella" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Selaginella microdonta" order="Selaginellales" pageId="17" pageNumber="110" phylum="Lycopodiophyta" rank="species" species="microdonta">
<emphasis id="5B58E979B51DAEBFA79E64620D022079" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="110">Selaginella microdonta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was previously known only from Venezuela (
<bibRefCitation id="09C0FCDA96DE835A94EBE78E57C7DD40" author="Alston, AHG" journalOrPublisher="Bulletin of the British Museum (Natural History), Botany" pageId="19" pageNumber="112" pagination="233 - 330" refId="B2" refString="Alston, AHG, Jermy, AC, Rankin, JM, 1981. The genus Selaginella in tropical South America. Bulletin of the British Museum (Natural History), Botany 9: 233 - 330" title="The genus Selaginella in tropical South America." volume="9" year="1981">Alston et al. 1981</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="72F83F42A21B76D557984338360D29B9" author="Smith, AR" journalOrPublisher="Pteridophytes, Spermatophytes: Acanthaceae-Araceae" pageId="21" pageNumber="114" pagination="296 - 314" refId="B25" refString="Smith, AR, 1995. Selaginellaceae. Pteridophytes, Spermatophytes: Acanthaceae-Araceae Vol. 2: 296 - 314" title="Selaginellaceae." volume="Vol. 2" year="1995">Smith 1995</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="BD1FF0FE3E800A9A97C58621DBF61C3A" author="Cremers, G" editor="Funk, V" journalOrPublisher="Contributions from the United States National Herbarium" pageId="19" pageNumber="112" pagination="17 - 56" refId="B4" refString="Cremers, G, Hickey, RJ, Lellinger, DB, Mickel, JT, Moran, RC, Ollgaard, B, Smith, AR, 2007. Pteridophytes &amp; allies. In: Funk, V, Hollowell, T, Berry, P, Kelloff, C, Alexander, SN, Eds., Checklist of the plants of the Guiana Shield (Venezuela: Amazonas, Bolivar, Delta Amacuro; Guyana, Surinam, French Guiana). Contributions from the United States National Herbarium 55: 17 - 56" title="Pteridophytes &amp; allies." volume="55" volumeTitle="Checklist of the plants of the Guiana Shield (Venezuela: Amazonas, Bolivar, Delta Amacuro; Guyana, Surinam, French Guiana)." year="2007">Cremers et al. 2007</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="6670D283897BFAFB3CA4391CE4DE42CA" author="Mostacero, J" editor="Hokche, O" journalOrPublisher="Fundacion Instituto Botanico de Venezuela, Caracas" pageId="20" pageNumber="113" pagination="167 - 170" refId="B17" refString="Mostacero, J, 2008. Selaginellaceae. In: Hokche, O, Berry, PE, Huber, O, Eds., Nuevo catalogo de la flora vascular de Venezuela. Fundacion Instituto Botanico de Venezuela, Caracas: 167 - 170" title="Selaginellaceae." volumeTitle="Nuevo catalogo de la flora vascular de Venezuela." year="2008">Mostacero 2008</bibRefCitation>
); its range is now extended to include Brazil. This species is characterized by being a minute, creeping plant with coriaceous leaves, the median leaves ovate, ovate-deltate with oblique to rounded bases with the outer ones prominent. Furthermore, these leaves have prominent, often arcuate midribs (making the halves of the laminae unequal), serrate to serrulate margins, and acute apices; the lateral leaves are broadly ovate-elliptic with thickened margins, these denticulate to entire, and acute apices tipped by 1-3 teeth. In Brazil, 
<taxonomicName id="CDFDD96023CFFF9287A939BFD4F3651A" class="Lycopodiopsida" family="Selaginellaceae" genus="Selaginella" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Selaginella microdonta" order="Selaginellales" pageId="17" pageNumber="110" phylum="Lycopodiophyta" rank="species" species="microdonta">
<emphasis id="E6E280D8AAE44D594B03D4059BE1CCBE" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="110">Selaginella microdonta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
may be confused with 
<taxonomicName id="F923977467DDB3FE724920A52736A71E" authorityName="Alston" authorityYear="1981" class="Lycopodiopsida" family="Selaginellaceae" genus="Selaginella" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Selaginella wurdackii" order="Selaginellales" pageId="17" pageNumber="110" phylum="Lycopodiophyta" rank="species" species="wurdackii">
<emphasis id="9FF3A4734B0E72327D3410B267B3E71B" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="110">Selaginella wurdackii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, from which it differs by its creeping habit and smaller median leaves with acute apices. According to 
<bibRefCitation id="DB804B2003E07C78AF5E656AF4D90561" author="Valdespino, IA" journalOrPublisher="Brittonia" pageId="21" pageNumber="114" pagination="199 - 207" publicationUrl="10.2307/2806833" refId="B30" refString="Valdespino, IA, 1992. New species of Selaginella (Selaginellaceae) from the Guayana Highland of Venezuela. Brittonia 44: 199 - 207, DOI: 10.2307/2806833" title="New species of Selaginella (Selaginellaceae) from the Guayana Highland of Venezuela." url="10.2307/2806833" volume="44" year="1992">Valdespino (1992)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<taxonomicName id="C26BDCF2F839E705E19D884C3A097672" class="Lycopodiopsida" family="Selaginellaceae" genus="Selaginella" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Selaginella microdonta" order="Selaginellales" pageId="17" pageNumber="110" phylum="Lycopodiophyta" rank="species" species="microdonta">
<emphasis id="953683CA52D454B191EDE9BCCE7AC372" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="110">Selaginella microdonta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is morphologically related to 
<taxonomicName id="54B795A794F6026579BB7FE43E8C7AB6" authorityName="Valdespino" authorityYear="1992" class="Lycopodiopsida" family="Selaginellaceae" genus="Selaginella" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Selaginella cardiophylla" order="Selaginellales" pageId="17" pageNumber="110" phylum="Lycopodiophyta" rank="species" species="cardiophylla">
<emphasis id="AD7A218BE5B74196FEACBDEDC38C83EB" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="110">Selaginella cardiophylla</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Valdespino and 
<taxonomicName id="602E76412CAFAD5D7425F4573E843BE1" authorityName="Valdespino" authorityYear="1992" class="Lycopodiopsida" family="Selaginellaceae" genus="Selaginella" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Selaginella hemicardia" order="Selaginellales" pageId="17" pageNumber="110" phylum="Lycopodiophyta" rank="species" species="hemicardia">
<emphasis id="C829D94670BE628AD3C96861B34A40B7" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="110">Selaginella hemicardia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Valdespino. The possible interrelationships and distinguishing characters are further discussed in 
<bibRefCitation id="17DA72754F1564F2C64C9EAA74801D9E" author="Valdespino, IA" journalOrPublisher="Brittonia" pageId="21" pageNumber="114" pagination="199 - 207" publicationUrl="10.2307/2806833" refId="B30" refString="Valdespino, IA, 1992. New species of Selaginella (Selaginellaceae) from the Guayana Highland of Venezuela. Brittonia 44: 199 - 207, DOI: 10.2307/2806833" title="New species of Selaginella (Selaginellaceae) from the Guayana Highland of Venezuela." url="10.2307/2806833" volume="44" year="1992">Valdespino (1992)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
